article.headline: Eastern Kentucky 73, Eastern Illinois 57
article.story: CHARLESTON, Ill. (AP) -- Jamaal Douglas' 16 points led four Eastern Kentucky players in double figures as the Colonels topped Eastern Illinois 73-57 Monday night. Mike Rose scored 14 points, Adam Leonard 13 and Julian Mascoll had 10 for Eastern Kentucky (7-3, 2-1 Ohio Valley), which had a 35-25 halftime advantage and led by as many as 26 points with just under 8:00 to go in the game. Eastern Illinois (4-7, 1-3) was led by 15 points from Romain Martin despite his 0-for-5 shooting from three-point range. Bobby Catchings and Jake Byrne added 11 points each for the Panthers, who finished 0-for-12 from behind the arc. The Colonels lost the rebounding battle 36-30, but managed 18 points off 14 Panther turnovers.
